WEBVTT

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:37.280
Let me introduce this to you.

00:01:37.480 --> 00:01:40.040
This one is our store's versatile bag.

00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:42.239
It suits your temperament perfectly.

00:01:42.239 --> 00:01:43.599
And it's also very fitting for your wife.

00:01:43.599 --> 00:01:44.239
How about this?

00:01:44.239 --> 00:01:45.599
Let me take it out for you to see.

00:01:45.599 --> 00:01:47.120
No, no, it's fine, it's fine. No need.

00:01:47.120 --> 00:01:49.200
I'll... I'll just look around first. Thank you.

00:01:49.799 --> 00:01:50.439
Okay.

00:02:19.520 --> 00:02:20.240
Swing it.

00:02:20.240 --> 00:02:22.000
Yes, yes, swing it, swing it!

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:22.800
Xuanxuan!

00:02:25.439 --> 00:02:26.199
Coming!

00:02:26.800 --> 00:02:28.360
Why did you bring them here?

00:02:28.360 --> 00:02:29.360
No, school's out.

00:02:29.360 --> 00:02:30.479
Just taking them out to play for a bit.

00:02:30.479 --> 00:02:31.240
What's wrong?

00:02:33.039 --> 00:02:35.680
Xuanxuan, is your homework finished?

00:02:37.879 --> 00:02:39.159
What did Mom say?

00:02:39.960 --> 00:02:42.120
After school, you do your homework first, right?

00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:43.680
Only after finishing homework can you play.

00:02:44.360 --> 00:02:46.479
What do you call it when you don't keep a promise?

00:02:46.639 --> 00:02:48.159
Breaking your word.

00:02:48.479 --> 00:02:51.439
Mom, I'm sorry. I was wrong.

00:02:51.800 --> 00:02:52.879
Hey, Boss Dong.

00:02:53.039 --> 00:02:54.759
The kids are having fun.

00:02:54.759 --> 00:02:55.560
Is that really necessary?

00:02:55.560 --> 00:02:56.520
What do you know?

00:02:56.520 --> 00:02:58.199
This is a matter of principle.

00:02:58.199 --> 00:02:59.479
Good habits are hard to form.

00:02:59.479 --> 00:03:01.120
Bad habits are learned in an instant.

00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:03.360
Unlike some people.

00:03:03.360 --> 00:03:05.360
Who act all high and mighty on the surface.

00:03:05.360 --> 00:03:06.680
But turn around and kneel without a second thought.

00:03:06.680 --> 00:03:07.199
I...

00:03:09.159 --> 00:03:09.800
Come here.

00:03:10.520 --> 00:03:11.759
Not in front of the kids.

00:03:14.479 --> 00:03:15.960
Business is business.

00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:18.520
Mixing personal and professional, *that's* a principle problem.

00:03:19.520 --> 00:03:21.039
Don't say I didn't warn you.

00:03:21.319 --> 00:03:23.840
Brothers in business, bound to fail.

00:03:24.560 --> 00:03:25.840
What nonsense are you spouting?

00:03:26.280 --> 00:03:27.400
If you have free time,

00:03:27.400 --> 00:03:28.719
spend more time with Xuanxuan.

00:03:29.280 --> 00:03:30.800
When your son resents you,

00:03:30.919 --> 00:03:32.159
then you'll know regret.

00:03:32.639 --> 00:03:34.400
Our child is none of your business.

00:03:35.159 --> 00:03:36.680
Xuanxuan, let's go.

00:03:37.199 --> 00:03:38.199
Mom...

00:03:40.280 --> 00:03:40.840
Let's go.

00:03:41.240 --> 00:03:42.560
Bye, Uncle.

00:03:42.719 --> 00:03:43.879
Bye, Xuanxuan.

00:03:44.000 --> 00:03:45.120
Goodbye.

00:03:56.800 --> 00:03:57.639
Son.

00:03:57.840 --> 00:03:59.400
Are you mad at Mom?

00:04:00.080 --> 00:04:03.199
I'm mad at myself for not resisting temptation.

00:04:03.199 --> 00:04:07.800
I just wanted to play a little longer with Yuanyuan.

00:04:07.800 --> 00:04:10.000
Mom never said you couldn't play.

00:04:10.000 --> 00:04:10.800
But the condition is,

00:04:10.800 --> 00:04:13.120
you have to finish your homework first.

00:04:14.560 --> 00:04:16.399
But today is also Mom's fault.

00:04:16.399 --> 00:04:17.439
I was late.

00:04:17.439 --> 00:04:19.000
It delayed your homework time.

00:04:19.199 --> 00:04:21.079
Mom will also say sorry to you, okay?

00:04:22.199 --> 00:04:23.439
I promise that from now on,

00:04:23.439 --> 00:04:25.560
this won't happen again.

00:04:25.639 --> 00:04:28.000
Good boy. I believe in you.

00:04:29.079 --> 00:04:30.000
What do you want for dinner?

00:04:30.000 --> 00:04:31.439
Mom will make you something delicious.

00:04:32.759 --> 00:04:33.639
Steak.

00:04:34.120 --> 00:04:35.879
Steak? Okay.

00:04:47.319 --> 00:04:49.519
How much longer are you going to polish those shoes?

00:04:49.519 --> 00:04:50.920
Hurry up and wash up for bed.

00:04:51.800 --> 00:04:53.279
I was just thinking,

00:04:53.279 --> 00:04:54.800
when Feifei comes back and sees all his shoes

00:04:54.800 --> 00:04:56.240
nice and clean.

00:05:02.720 --> 00:05:03.560
You scared me.

00:05:03.560 --> 00:05:05.480
What are you so absent-minded about?

00:05:14.040 --> 00:05:15.639
I wonder how Feifei is doing now.

00:05:17.079 --> 00:05:19.759
Why did you have to confiscate the kid's phone?

00:05:20.319 --> 00:05:21.560
I want to call the kid,

00:05:21.560 --> 00:05:23.199
ask how he is, but I can't even do that.

00:05:23.879 --> 00:05:24.920
Tell me about it.

00:05:28.639 --> 00:05:29.519
No, I mean,

00:05:30.639 --> 00:05:31.879
That Ma Weiguo jerk,

00:05:31.879 --> 00:05:33.680
is he messing with me again?

00:05:35.480 --> 00:05:36.800
You're something else.

00:05:36.800 --> 00:05:37.920
When things are good,

00:05:37.920 --> 00:05:39.560
Ma Weiguo is your sworn brother.

00:05:39.560 --> 00:05:40.560
When things are bad,

00:05:40.560 --> 00:05:42.279
Ma Weiguo becomes your grandson.

00:05:47.879 --> 00:05:49.600
That place is so poor,

00:05:50.120 --> 00:05:52.240
Feifei's bound to lose weight from hunger.

00:05:53.519 --> 00:05:55.160
Wasn't it you who insisted

00:05:55.160 --> 00:05:57.160
on sending the kid there to toughen up?

00:06:03.680 --> 00:06:04.759
I'm tired. Going to sleep.

00:06:06.879 --> 00:06:07.839
Hold on a second.

00:06:08.000 --> 00:06:09.519
Your hands, you just finished polishing shoes.

00:06:09.519 --> 00:06:10.800
Go wash them before getting into bed.

00:06:10.800 --> 00:06:11.720
Aren't they dirty?

00:06:11.720 --> 00:06:13.360
I'm exhausted.

00:06:15.439 --> 00:06:16.680
No, no, forget it, forget it.

00:06:16.680 --> 00:06:17.680
I'll sleep in Feifei's room.

00:06:17.839 --> 00:06:18.639
You stay right there.

00:06:19.519 --> 00:06:20.519
No, the kid's not home.

00:06:20.519 --> 00:06:22.720
What, are you going to sleep in separate rooms now?

00:06:22.720 --> 00:06:24.560
Is it just because I said your roast isn't as good as Grandpa's?

00:06:24.560 --> 00:06:25.920
Is it worth getting this angry?

00:06:25.920 --> 00:06:27.680
What does Grandpa have to do with this?

00:06:27.680 --> 00:06:29.439
Don't take your anger out on me.

00:06:31.079 --> 00:06:32.399
Just hurry up and wash up for bed.

00:06:40.319 --> 00:06:41.519
What are you standing there for?

00:06:41.639 --> 00:06:42.680
Don't know where to sleep?

00:06:42.680 --> 00:06:43.639
Then sleep standing up.

00:07:19.040 --> 00:07:20.519
Let's play a game.

00:07:21.040 --> 00:07:23.000
Tell about a stupid thing you've done.

00:07:23.160 --> 00:07:24.600
The really, really stupid kind.

00:07:24.600 --> 00:07:25.639
The loser drinks.

00:07:27.199 --> 00:07:28.639
Cleaning a toilet in a suit.

00:07:28.839 --> 00:07:29.519
Does that count?

00:07:29.959 --> 00:07:30.639
What?

00:07:32.839 --> 00:07:33.759
Martin.

00:07:33.759 --> 00:07:36.279
The company isn't doing well now.

00:07:36.279 --> 00:07:38.839
So we had to let all the janitors go.

00:07:38.959 --> 00:07:41.399
It's really hard for me to ask this,

00:07:41.560 --> 00:07:44.199
but could you please, after finishing work each day,

00:07:44.199 --> 00:07:47.120
also clean the toilets?

00:07:47.120 --> 00:07:50.680
Even though there's no extra pay,

00:07:50.680 --> 00:07:52.399
we all really like you.

00:07:52.560 --> 00:07:55.079
You're very good at this job.

00:07:55.160 --> 00:07:56.639
You actually believed that?

00:07:56.879 --> 00:07:58.639
You're really stupid.

00:07:59.199 --> 00:08:00.560
That year was 2008.

00:08:00.759 --> 00:08:01.800
I told myself,

00:08:02.279 --> 00:08:03.360
to accept it.

00:08:04.199 --> 00:08:05.879
They really did have their difficulties.

00:08:07.560 --> 00:08:08.800
But a month later,

00:08:09.160 --> 00:08:10.399
people started complaining

00:08:10.480 --> 00:08:12.240
about why there were water stains on the sink.

00:08:12.399 --> 00:08:13.519
A month and a half later,

00:08:13.639 --> 00:08:14.920
these people told me

00:08:15.079 --> 00:08:16.759
today's trash bag wasn't tied.

00:08:16.839 --> 00:08:18.399
Take your things and get out.

00:08:19.680 --> 00:08:22.560
Afterwards, I was understandably depressed for a long time.

00:08:22.560 --> 00:08:24.680
For the longest time, I couldn't figure out

00:08:24.759 --> 00:08:26.360
whether fake kindness or unkindness

00:08:26.839 --> 00:08:28.279
is ultimately more deadly.

00:08:52.639 --> 00:08:53.159
Jing.

00:08:53.159 --> 00:08:53.799
Give it to me.

00:09:09.120 --> 00:09:11.600
There's nothing wrong with this duck.

00:09:18.879 --> 00:09:20.080
No problem.

00:09:27.120 --> 00:09:28.080
Weiguo.

00:09:28.240 --> 00:09:29.600
So, are you still investing?

00:09:30.480 --> 00:09:32.440
Yes, of course I am.

00:09:32.759 --> 00:09:34.519
But the three issues I raised

00:09:34.519 --> 00:09:35.559
must all be resolved.

00:09:35.559 --> 00:09:36.360
Then I'll invest.

00:09:36.480 --> 00:09:37.679
That's no problem.

00:09:37.679 --> 00:09:39.759
Actually, I just think Big Brother is out of practice.

00:09:39.759 --> 00:09:40.120
Right.

00:09:40.120 --> 00:09:40.720
He just needs to practice.

00:09:40.720 --> 00:09:41.559
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

00:09:41.759 --> 00:09:42.360
I think so too.

00:09:42.360 --> 00:09:43.240
Here's what we'll do.

00:09:44.000 --> 00:09:46.519
Since Weiguo yesterday

00:09:46.919 --> 00:09:49.120
pointed out flaws with the duck,

00:09:49.120 --> 00:09:51.279
I'll make another one later, okay?

00:09:51.279 --> 00:09:52.519
Big Brother, you don't need to.

00:09:54.919 --> 00:09:56.240
It'll be the same even if you make another.

00:10:00.679 --> 00:10:01.799
I think we should do this.

00:10:01.919 --> 00:10:03.240
Starting tomorrow,

00:10:03.240 --> 00:10:04.919
we'll find the twenty most popular,

00:10:04.919 --> 00:10:07.559
most distinctive roast duck restaurants in Beijing online.

00:10:07.759 --> 00:10:08.879
We'll visit each one.

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:11.039
To learn their strengths.

00:10:11.039 --> 00:10:11.639
How about it?

00:10:12.919 --> 00:10:13.639
Weiguo,

00:10:13.840 --> 00:10:16.679
can those trendy spots compare to our Peng Le Xuan?

00:10:16.679 --> 00:10:18.559
Can they compare to your Big Brother's skill?

00:10:18.679 --> 00:10:19.279
No, Weiguo,

00:10:19.279 --> 00:10:21.679
you're kind of embarrassing me here.

00:10:21.799 --> 00:10:24.039
Big Brother, you said

00:10:24.039 --> 00:10:25.399
no matter what request I make,

00:10:25.399 --> 00:10:26.679
you'd do your best to cooperate.

00:10:26.679 --> 00:10:28.039
Yes, but I think

00:10:28.039 --> 00:10:29.679
the practical issue now is

00:10:29.679 --> 00:10:30.639
this process will take

00:10:30.639 --> 00:10:31.720
at least eight to ten days.

00:10:31.720 --> 00:10:34.000
And those places listed online aren't reliable.

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:34.399
Right.

00:10:34.399 --> 00:10:36.039
Isn't Lianbao familiar with the restaurant business?

00:10:36.039 --> 00:10:37.200
These twenty duck restaurants

00:10:37.200 --> 00:10:38.399
will be compiled by him.

00:10:38.679 --> 00:10:41.320
Big Brother will go taste-test them one by one.

00:10:41.320 --> 00:10:43.879
After each one, write a review.

00:10:44.039 --> 00:10:45.679
Strengths and weaknesses must be included.

00:10:46.279 --> 00:10:47.559
Aren't we trying to improve?

00:10:47.559 --> 00:10:49.440
We must learn from others' strengths, right?

00:10:50.480 --> 00:10:52.399
Are you okay?

00:10:52.799 --> 00:10:53.440
Big Brother, Big Brother.

00:10:53.440 --> 00:10:54.320
No, I mean, Ma Weiguo,

00:10:54.519 --> 00:10:56.360
what grand scheme are you planning?

00:10:56.440 --> 00:10:57.480
Not just Big Brother,

00:10:57.559 --> 00:10:59.080
the three of us have to go too.

00:10:59.840 --> 00:11:01.200
I'm going to Xi'an.

00:11:01.399 --> 00:11:02.559
Whoever wants to go can go.

00:11:02.559 --> 00:11:03.559
I'm not playing along.

00:11:03.559 --> 00:11:05.320
Don't forget, I have veto power.

00:11:05.519 --> 00:11:06.519
If you want to do this, listen to me.

00:11:06.519 --> 00:11:07.480
Unless you don't want to.

00:11:12.600 --> 00:11:13.360
Weiguo,

00:11:16.080 --> 00:11:17.720
can I make a small suggestion?

00:11:17.799 --> 00:11:18.279
Speak.

00:11:19.000 --> 00:11:22.159
In the future, when you talk to us brothers,

00:11:22.279 --> 00:11:23.960
try to watch your tone a bit.

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:27.759
Brother Qiu'er,

00:11:28.639 --> 00:11:30.080
I'd like to trouble you.

00:11:30.320 --> 00:11:31.759
Tomorrow at noon, twelve o'clock,

00:11:31.759 --> 00:11:34.039
we'll gather on time at Peng Le Xuan's entrance.

00:11:34.039 --> 00:11:34.759
Is that okay?

00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:37.240
Thank you, Brother Qiu'er.

00:11:37.679 --> 00:11:38.960
I'll take my leave now.

00:11:39.799 --> 00:11:40.759
See you tomorrow at noon.

00:11:48.120 --> 00:11:50.399
Why do I feel a chill down my spine?

00:12:03.840 --> 00:12:06.399
Isn't this just asking for humiliation?

00:12:06.679 --> 00:12:07.799
Weaving my own cocoon.

00:12:07.799 --> 00:12:08.679
Bringing trouble on myself.

00:12:08.679 --> 00:12:09.879
Inviting a wolf into the house.

00:12:10.399 --> 00:12:12.440
What kind of nonsense is this?

00:12:12.799 --> 00:12:15.000
Using all the idioms I learned here.

00:12:15.000 --> 00:12:17.279
And here I was, speaking up for him all day.

00:12:17.279 --> 00:12:18.399
And what does the old gentleman do?

00:12:18.399 --> 00:12:21.159
Turns around and punches me in the chest.

00:12:22.759 --> 00:12:23.519
Tomorrow morning,

00:12:23.639 --> 00:12:24.840
I'm going out first thing.

00:12:24.840 --> 00:12:26.279
Tell them I have an emergency.

00:12:27.399 --> 00:12:28.200
You're not going?

00:12:28.200 --> 00:12:29.840
Why should I go?

00:12:33.399 --> 00:12:34.840
You're quick with your hands.

00:12:35.039 --> 00:12:36.320
This is alcohol.

00:12:36.519 --> 00:12:38.360
Fine, feeling down, have a drink.

00:12:39.519 --> 00:12:40.759
But if you ask me,

00:12:40.919 --> 00:12:42.000
you should go.

00:12:42.240 --> 00:12:43.080
No.

00:12:48.440 --> 00:12:50.840
What did you tell Feifei?

00:12:50.919 --> 00:12:52.759
Aren't you supposed to set an example for Feifei?

00:12:52.919 --> 00:12:54.080
You said it yourself,

00:12:54.080 --> 00:12:55.039
Feifei is in that place,

00:12:55.039 --> 00:12:56.480
how much hardship he must endure.

00:12:56.480 --> 00:12:57.879
You've barely started,

00:12:57.879 --> 00:12:59.320
and you're already backing down?

00:12:59.480 --> 00:13:01.320
What will Feifei think of you?

00:13:01.840 --> 00:13:03.120
What do you mean, think of me?

00:13:03.120 --> 00:13:04.600
How dare he think anything of me?

00:13:05.519 --> 00:13:06.519
He's young.

00:13:06.519 --> 00:13:07.879
He should endure some hardship.

00:13:07.879 --> 00:13:08.799
But me now,

00:13:08.799 --> 00:13:09.799
I, I'm going looking for hardship?

00:13:09.799 --> 00:13:11.759
Am I sick? Am I stupid?

00:13:11.879 --> 00:13:12.639
I'm not going.

00:13:14.080 --> 00:13:14.720
Alright.

00:13:15.759 --> 00:13:17.039
If you won't go, you won't go.

00:13:20.080 --> 00:13:21.559
No, no, you drink, you drink.

00:13:24.960 --> 00:13:26.200
I just won't go.

00:13:26.559 --> 00:13:28.080
Even if you beat me to death, I won't go.

00:13:28.279 --> 00:13:30.960
Right, even if I beat you to death, you won't go.

00:13:33.360 --> 00:13:34.279
Eat.

00:13:38.159 --> 00:13:38.919
Don't want to.

00:13:44.960 --> 00:13:45.720
You know what,

00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:46.600
this little room of yours,

00:13:46.600 --> 00:13:47.360
with all your fussing,

00:13:47.360 --> 00:13:48.799
is actually quite nice.

00:13:50.519 --> 00:13:51.879
I know what you want to say.

00:13:52.279 --> 00:13:53.559
I've said all I needed to say.

00:13:53.840 --> 00:13:55.759
See, you've misunderstood me.

00:13:56.000 --> 00:13:56.799
Really, Weiguo,

00:13:56.799 --> 00:13:59.279
yesterday I was deeply impressed by your presence.

00:13:59.279 --> 00:14:00.360
Your image in my mind

00:14:00.360 --> 00:14:01.879
has become tall and mighty again.

00:14:02.000 --> 00:14:03.279
Look at President Xie, such a big boss,

00:14:03.279 --> 00:14:04.600
acting like a grandson in front of you.

00:14:04.600 --> 00:14:05.480
With you here,

00:14:05.480 --> 00:14:07.200
this duck restaurant venture is sure to succeed.

00:14:11.559 --> 00:14:13.240
You, having Big Brother do the taste-testing,

00:14:13.240 --> 00:14:14.840
I think is absolutely right.

00:14:15.120 --> 00:14:16.200
If he doesn't try other food,

00:14:16.200 --> 00:14:16.840
how can he know

00:14:16.840 --> 00:14:18.360
where his own problems lie?

00:14:18.799 --> 00:14:21.519
The only thing is a small, small suggestion.

00:14:22.320 --> 00:14:25.679
Could we skip writing those taste-test summaries?

00:14:25.679 --> 00:14:27.639
Do you think with Big Brother's temper he'll write them?

00:14:27.639 --> 00:14:28.879
Big Brother isn't your employee.

00:14:28.879 --> 00:14:30.039
Tomorrow at noon, twelve o'clock,

00:14:30.039 --> 00:14:31.000
don't be late.

00:14:34.440 --> 00:14:35.399
So it was all for nothing.

00:14:59.879 --> 00:15:01.039
Still awake?

00:15:01.679 --> 00:15:04.360
Me? I'll sleep in a bit.

00:15:04.519 --> 00:15:05.559
Just a little while.

00:15:06.120 --> 00:15:08.039
Sleep, sleep. Come on, you sleep.

00:15:08.039 --> 00:15:09.600
You sleep. Go to sleep.

00:15:10.799 --> 00:15:13.639
I'll sleep too. Sleep.

00:15:44.559 --> 00:15:45.519
Auntie Tong, what's wrong?

00:15:45.600 --> 00:15:46.440
Weiguo.

00:15:46.600 --> 00:15:48.639
Your uncle has been restless all night.

00:15:48.919 --> 00:15:50.360
Not good. Maybe...

00:15:50.360 --> 00:15:51.440
Don't worry. I'll take him to the hospital.

00:15:51.440 --> 00:15:51.799
Okay.

00:15:51.799 --> 00:15:53.000
Wait a moment. Let me grab a coat.

00:16:13.440 --> 00:16:14.879
Why didn't you say anything?

00:16:15.440 --> 00:16:17.039
Why didn't you tell me?

00:16:17.039 --> 00:16:18.720
It's already been two years!

00:16:18.720 --> 00:16:19.559
I knew nothing about it.

00:16:19.559 --> 00:16:21.320
It's not a serious illness. Don't panic.

00:16:27.679 --> 00:16:29.600
How sick do you have to be for it to be serious?

00:16:29.799 --> 00:16:31.159
Only when you're stone dead, is that it?

00:16:31.159 --> 00:16:32.200
Stop wailing!

00:16:32.200 --> 00:16:34.200
See how annoying you are?

00:16:34.200 --> 00:16:35.120
*I'm* annoying?

00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:36.559
You're the one driving me crazy!

00:16:36.559 --> 00:16:38.559
Alright, alright, this is a hospital.

00:16:38.559 --> 00:16:40.720
Let's keep our voices down. We can talk at home, okay?

00:16:40.720 --> 00:16:42.600
See if you'll stay up late again.

00:16:51.519 --> 00:16:52.240
Kid.

00:16:53.080 --> 00:16:54.279
What's on your mind?

00:16:55.440 --> 00:16:56.200
Nothing.

00:16:56.960 --> 00:16:59.320
I was thinking about you being sick and not telling Tong Qiu.

00:16:59.399 --> 00:17:00.480
What would he think?

00:17:00.960 --> 00:17:03.639
Kid, you mustn't tell him.

00:17:03.879 --> 00:17:04.799
Some things...

00:17:04.799 --> 00:17:06.319
...are better if he doesn't know.

00:17:06.960 --> 00:17:09.680
Not everyone needs to know the truth.

00:17:10.960 --> 00:17:12.200
It's like...

00:17:12.200 --> 00:17:14.799
...standing on top of the China World Tower.

00:17:15.319 --> 00:17:16.759
You look around.

00:17:16.759 --> 00:17:19.680
Everywhere you see are skyscrapers.

00:17:20.200 --> 00:17:24.680
A sea of glass walls, digital screens, ads.

00:17:24.839 --> 00:17:27.920
A beautiful view of the world at your feet.

00:17:28.000 --> 00:17:29.519
But then you look again.

00:17:29.680 --> 00:17:31.799
At the very bottom, on the ground.

00:17:31.799 --> 00:17:34.079
There's still a little bit...

00:17:34.079 --> 00:17:36.519
...of those shabby little bungalows.

00:17:37.400 --> 00:17:39.079
Sometimes, when your perspective is high,

00:17:39.079 --> 00:17:40.400
you can look down.

00:17:40.400 --> 00:17:42.279
But if you're standing at the bottom,

00:17:42.279 --> 00:17:43.599
you don't necessarily need to know

00:17:43.599 --> 00:17:45.759
what it looks like up top.

00:17:47.599 --> 00:17:48.599
Don't talk nonsense.

00:17:48.599 --> 00:17:50.799
I know you've had some schooling.

00:17:50.799 --> 00:17:52.559
Know how to write a script.

00:17:55.680 --> 00:17:56.480
Weiguo.

00:17:57.119 --> 00:17:59.599
What you said to me the other day was spot on.

00:18:00.039 --> 00:18:03.160
This is my last chance to focus on writing.

00:18:03.160 --> 00:18:05.240
I have to cherish it.

00:18:06.359 --> 00:18:07.559
I'm sorry, Uncle Tong.

00:18:08.400 --> 00:18:09.680
I spoke too offensively.

00:18:09.680 --> 00:18:10.440
No, no, no.

00:18:10.640 --> 00:18:12.359
You were absolutely right.

00:18:13.279 --> 00:18:16.079
Your words woke me from my dream.

00:18:16.519 --> 00:18:18.559
All that "CEO falls in love" stuff...

00:18:18.559 --> 00:18:21.079
...should be left to those who are good at it.

00:18:21.079 --> 00:18:21.799
As for me...

00:18:21.799 --> 00:18:24.519
...I should go back and visit these old neighbors,

00:18:24.519 --> 00:18:25.640
these old pals.

00:18:25.640 --> 00:18:28.480
You're really not as good as those kids.

00:18:28.480 --> 00:18:31.920
You always talk about how great the hutong stories are.

00:18:31.920 --> 00:18:33.440
No chance to write them.

00:18:33.440 --> 00:18:35.079
Just wasting time for nothing.

00:18:36.039 --> 00:18:37.119
Right, right, right.

00:18:37.400 --> 00:18:40.200
The last script of my life...

00:18:40.279 --> 00:18:43.039
...should be written for myself.

00:18:57.279 --> 00:18:58.839
What time is it now?

00:18:59.599 --> 00:19:00.440
Where is everyone?

00:19:00.440 --> 00:19:02.000
No sense of time?

00:19:03.799 --> 00:19:05.480
Didn't you two say you weren't going?

00:19:06.880 --> 00:19:07.480
Why are you so...

00:19:07.480 --> 00:19:08.519
Why do you have so much to say?

00:19:08.519 --> 00:19:09.880
You're the one who talks too much.

00:19:31.000 --> 00:19:31.839
They said since you were little,

00:19:31.839 --> 00:19:32.880
you loved this brand of soda.

00:19:32.880 --> 00:19:33.920
Bought you some.

00:19:39.160 --> 00:19:40.160
Actually...

00:19:41.440 --> 00:19:42.960
...I came to apologize to you.

00:19:42.960 --> 00:19:45.440
Last time, I spoke a bit harshly.

00:19:47.319 --> 00:19:49.440
Actually, after observing you this past while,

00:19:49.440 --> 00:19:51.359
I think you have a good heart,

00:19:51.359 --> 00:19:52.880
and very sharp opinions.

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:54.000
For example,

00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:54.960
with Grandpa Tong's script,

00:19:54.960 --> 00:19:56.920
you pointed out a better direction.

00:19:56.920 --> 00:19:58.920
Or, with Uncle Wang's declining skills,

00:19:58.920 --> 00:20:00.319
you'd tell him clearly.

00:20:01.039 --> 00:20:02.480
You didn't come just for this, did you?

00:20:02.480 --> 00:20:03.359
There you go again.

00:20:03.960 --> 00:20:06.440
You're both proud and tsundere.

00:20:06.440 --> 00:20:08.119
Always saying one thing and meaning another.

00:20:08.119 --> 00:20:09.839
Just secretly enjoy the praise.

00:20:09.839 --> 00:20:11.880
But you always act like you don't need it.

00:20:12.160 --> 00:20:12.960
And also...

00:20:13.200 --> 00:20:14.680
I know you came back this time

00:20:14.680 --> 00:20:16.359
actually wanting to make up with them.

00:20:16.359 --> 00:20:17.000
But...

00:20:17.000 --> 00:20:18.960
You wait for others to give you an out.

00:20:19.079 --> 00:20:20.319
What if they don't give you one?

00:20:20.319 --> 00:20:21.519
You still have to make one yourself.

00:20:21.519 --> 00:20:22.279
Ma Weiguo!

00:20:23.160 --> 00:20:24.160
Ma Weiguo!

00:20:25.319 --> 00:20:26.039
Don't speak.

00:20:26.839 --> 00:20:28.160
What are you dawdling for?

00:20:28.519 --> 00:20:29.920
You set the time yourself.

00:20:30.039 --> 00:20:31.200
Need an invitation?

00:20:31.359 --> 00:20:32.440
No, I have an upset stomach.

00:20:32.440 --> 00:20:33.400
It'll be better soon.

00:20:33.559 --> 00:20:34.960
A lazy donkey has many excuses.

00:20:34.960 --> 00:20:35.680
Hurry up!

00:20:35.880 --> 00:20:36.759
Very soon!

00:20:42.160 --> 00:20:43.400
Who would've thought...

00:20:43.400 --> 00:20:45.039
...you're quite scared of my uncle.

00:20:47.559 --> 00:20:49.720
Actually, besides apologizing, I came

00:20:49.720 --> 00:20:51.200
to discuss a collaboration with you.

00:20:51.200 --> 00:20:52.640
We can exchange benefits.

00:20:53.680 --> 00:20:54.440
You, see...

00:20:54.440 --> 00:20:55.839
...you offend people as soon as you open your mouth.

00:20:55.839 --> 00:20:56.960
But I'm not like you.

00:20:56.960 --> 00:20:57.880
I'm well-liked.

00:20:57.880 --> 00:20:59.039
And clever as ice and snow.

00:20:59.319 --> 00:21:01.079
So I think I can help you with that.

00:21:01.079 --> 00:21:03.160
I can let you keep your tsundere side

00:21:03.160 --> 00:21:05.079
while also keeping the uncles happy.

00:21:06.200 --> 00:21:08.359
But if you want my help, there's a condition.

00:21:08.960 --> 00:21:11.640
I'm holding a photo exhibition and need to go on location.

00:21:11.640 --> 00:21:13.759
So I need an assistant who knows Beijing

00:21:13.759 --> 00:21:15.359
and has nothing better to do.

00:21:15.359 --> 00:21:16.480
I think you're quite suitable.

00:21:17.119 --> 00:21:18.480
You want me to be your assistant?

00:21:18.480 --> 00:21:19.440
Are you out of your mind?

00:21:19.640 --> 00:21:20.440
Do you really think I'm that idle?

00:21:20.440 --> 00:21:22.079
I think you really are quite idle.

00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:24.200
Don't rush to refuse.

00:21:24.200 --> 00:21:25.319
Think it over and tell me.

00:21:25.319 --> 00:21:26.720
When you come around, look for me.

00:21:27.680 --> 00:21:29.640
No salary. Room and board on your own.

00:21:30.119 --> 00:21:31.119
No need to see me out.

00:21:46.480 --> 00:21:48.079
If you drink my soda, you have to agree.

00:21:48.079 --> 00:21:49.000
Promise me!

00:21:49.160 --> 00:21:50.079
I can't hear you!

00:22:00.400 --> 00:22:00.960
By the way,

00:22:03.279 --> 00:22:04.319
this is the roast duck shop

00:22:04.319 --> 00:22:06.000
that's been truly popular in Beijing these years.

00:22:06.200 --> 00:22:08.759
You can't just look at online rankings.

00:22:09.039 --> 00:22:11.599
I've personally handled many of those rankings.

00:22:12.240 --> 00:22:13.160
These here

00:22:13.279 --> 00:22:14.920
are the real backend data.

00:22:25.519 --> 00:22:27.079
Greetings to the four Lords.

00:22:27.079 --> 00:22:28.559
Before we dine,

00:22:28.559 --> 00:22:29.680
there is a changing service.

00:22:29.680 --> 00:22:30.400
Please come inside.

00:22:30.400 --> 00:22:32.200
Can't we just go straight in and be done with it?

00:22:32.200 --> 00:22:33.799
Just try it, see what it's like.

00:22:37.279 --> 00:22:38.839
Big Brother, look at Qiu'er.

00:22:38.839 --> 00:22:40.319
Doesn't he look like a noble young lord?

00:22:40.319 --> 00:22:42.559
I don't see the prince or noble lord look.

00:22:42.559 --> 00:22:44.000
He looks a bit like a grandson.

00:22:44.720 --> 00:22:45.799
Let's go.

00:22:47.799 --> 00:22:49.920
From the decor style to the operation model,

00:22:49.920 --> 00:22:50.920
including this tableware,

00:22:50.920 --> 00:22:52.160
it's all custom-made.

00:22:52.160 --> 00:22:54.160
It focuses on an immersive time-travel experience.

00:22:54.160 --> 00:22:56.519
Don't talk to me about immersive time-travel experiences.

00:22:56.519 --> 00:22:58.440
A restaurant is a place for eating.

00:22:58.440 --> 00:23:00.480
Eating is just eating.

00:23:02.400 --> 00:23:03.359
Smells pretty good.

00:23:03.359 --> 00:23:04.200
You don't say,

00:23:04.319 --> 00:23:05.559
the taste is actually quite good.

00:23:05.559 --> 00:23:06.920
What's so special about this?

00:23:06.920 --> 00:23:08.599
The vegetable market in our alley

00:23:08.599 --> 00:23:09.920
sells exactly the same thing.

00:23:09.920 --> 00:23:11.200
Anyway, I'm not eating it.

00:23:12.319 --> 00:23:13.119
Big Brother.

00:23:13.240 --> 00:23:15.559
Seeing is deceiving, tasting is believing.

00:23:15.559 --> 00:23:17.160
Since we are here to taste test,

00:23:17.160 --> 00:23:18.880
how will you know if it's good if you don't eat?

00:23:27.720 --> 00:23:30.119
This sauce isn't from Liubiju.

00:23:30.119 --> 00:23:31.440
And speaking of these scallions,

00:23:31.440 --> 00:23:34.400
they definitely aren't Shandong lamb's horn scallions.

00:23:34.400 --> 00:23:35.160
And this too.

00:23:35.680 --> 00:23:36.960
They even served popping candy.

00:23:36.960 --> 00:23:37.400
What?

00:23:37.400 --> 00:23:37.880
Right.

00:23:38.000 --> 00:23:39.480
And their pancakes.

00:23:46.880 --> 00:23:47.440
Look.

00:23:47.640 --> 00:23:49.359
You have to ball it up,

00:23:49.359 --> 00:23:50.839
and it should open up with a snap.

00:23:50.839 --> 00:23:52.359
That's a proper pancake.

00:23:52.359 --> 00:23:53.359
Look at this duck again.

00:23:53.359 --> 00:23:55.559
The caramel color on this duck is a bit too dark.

00:23:55.559 --> 00:23:57.920
The meat's fat and lean ratio is uneven.

00:23:57.920 --> 00:23:58.759
And the knife work.

00:23:58.759 --> 00:24:00.480
Would you call this willow leaf style,

00:24:00.480 --> 00:24:01.880
or dough strip style?

00:24:01.880 --> 00:24:03.920
This... this is neither here nor there.

00:24:04.279 --> 00:24:05.079
Hello.

00:24:05.079 --> 00:24:06.640
Your roast duck is ready.

00:24:06.640 --> 00:24:08.400
I am Chef Number 27.

00:24:08.400 --> 00:24:09.680
I'm happy to serve you.

00:24:09.839 --> 00:24:10.880
We select

00:24:10.880 --> 00:24:13.200
ducklings that are about 22 days old.

00:24:13.279 --> 00:24:15.359
After air-drying and roasting,

00:24:15.359 --> 00:24:16.680
the skin is thick and the meat is tender.

00:24:16.839 --> 00:24:19.160
Sliced vertically into thin pieces, skin with meat.

00:24:19.720 --> 00:24:21.000
During the slicing process,

00:24:21.000 --> 00:24:24.039
we remove the fat between the skin and the meat.

00:24:24.039 --> 00:24:27.039
This allows diners to eat with health and peace of mind.

00:24:33.880 --> 00:24:36.799
So now they even remove the fat.

00:24:36.880 --> 00:24:37.920
In the past, when eating duck,

00:24:37.920 --> 00:24:39.200
people specifically picked the fatty parts.

00:24:40.160 --> 00:24:40.759
Of course,

00:24:40.759 --> 00:24:42.839
nowadays everything is low oil and low salt.

00:24:43.680 --> 00:24:44.319
Chef.

00:24:44.839 --> 00:24:46.240
How old are you this year?

00:24:46.240 --> 00:24:47.079
Thirty-two.

00:24:47.160 --> 00:24:48.440
But this skill in your hands

00:24:48.440 --> 00:24:50.240
is really no worse than many old masters.

00:24:50.359 --> 00:24:52.319
The chefs here are all about my age.

00:24:52.400 --> 00:24:53.079
Really?

00:24:53.920 --> 00:24:54.559
Chef,

00:24:54.920 --> 00:24:56.880
how did you all practice your craft?

00:24:56.880 --> 00:24:58.079
Is there any secret?

00:24:58.160 --> 00:24:59.880
Just practice.

00:24:59.880 --> 00:25:00.839
So, in this shop of yours,

00:25:00.839 --> 00:25:02.440
how many chefs are there like you?

00:25:03.119 --> 00:25:05.119
There are about thirty or so.

00:25:05.880 --> 00:25:07.559
But, but to be honest with you,

00:25:07.559 --> 00:25:10.119
my skill is considered average here.

00:25:10.519 --> 00:25:11.839
After we graduated from

00:25:11.839 --> 00:25:12.599
culinary school,

00:25:12.599 --> 00:25:15.240
every day is just roasting ducks and slicing ducks.

00:25:15.240 --> 00:25:16.960
We haven't stopped for over ten years.

00:25:16.960 --> 00:25:18.640
Especially after coming to our unit,

00:25:18.640 --> 00:25:19.920
we follow standardized service.

00:25:19.920 --> 00:25:21.400
We have to practice every day.

00:25:22.720 --> 00:25:25.480
Big Brother, what do you think?

00:25:26.920 --> 00:25:30.599
No, haven't we not eaten yet?

00:25:37.079 --> 00:25:37.960
I say, President Ma,

00:25:38.200 --> 00:25:40.000
shouldn't we speed things up?

00:25:40.519 --> 00:25:42.039
If you have trouble with that investment,

00:25:42.039 --> 00:25:43.359
ask for Big Brother's opinion.

00:25:43.680 --> 00:25:45.279
Big Brother is a professional, right?

00:25:47.559 --> 00:25:48.559
I think,

00:25:49.720 --> 00:25:51.000
generally speaking,

00:25:51.000 --> 00:25:52.079
it's alright.

00:25:52.759 --> 00:25:53.480
But look at this duck.

00:25:53.480 --> 00:25:53.880
Big Brother.

00:25:53.880 --> 00:25:54.559
Let me finish.

00:25:54.559 --> 00:25:54.960
Big Brother.

00:25:54.960 --> 00:25:55.720
It's a bit thin.

00:25:55.920 --> 00:25:57.440
We have to respect the facts.

00:25:57.960 --> 00:25:59.920
I think their duck is actually quite good.

00:25:59.920 --> 00:26:01.079
No, is it what you think,

00:26:01.079 --> 00:26:02.480
or what I think?

00:26:11.039 --> 00:26:12.119
Is it that delicious?

00:26:12.119 --> 00:26:14.200
I'll grab a bite and hurry to work.

00:26:21.599 --> 00:26:22.319
Honey

00:26:22.799 --> 00:26:24.440
This investment thing with Weiguo

00:26:24.440 --> 00:26:26.240
insists on doing this tasting event.

00:26:26.519 --> 00:26:27.559
You said you were coming,

00:26:27.559 --> 00:26:29.480
so I arranged all my work here.

00:26:29.480 --> 00:26:31.079
Now you can't make it, fine.

00:26:31.079 --> 00:26:32.400
But I can't even go back now.

00:26:32.400 --> 00:26:34.160
Can you be more reliable in the future?

00:26:34.160 --> 00:26:35.279
Yes, yes, yes.

00:26:35.279 --> 00:26:36.799
I... I... I couldn't help it.

00:26:36.799 --> 00:26:38.559
It was a complete accident.

00:26:38.759 --> 00:26:41.680
Your biggest strength is being easygoing.

00:26:41.680 --> 00:26:43.720
Your biggest flaw is being *too* easygoing.

00:26:43.720 --> 00:26:45.480
Could you, just once,

00:26:45.480 --> 00:26:47.160
plan things out properly?

00:26:47.160 --> 00:26:48.559
Even if something comes up last minute,

00:26:48.559 --> 00:26:50.240
you should have a backup plan.

00:26:50.480 --> 00:26:52.480
Yes, yes, my fault, my fault.

00:26:52.480 --> 00:26:54.960
When you get back, I'll make it up to you.

00:26:55.319 --> 00:26:56.359
And about having a baby...

00:26:56.359 --> 00:26:58.440
Am I talking about having a baby right now?

00:26:58.599 --> 00:26:59.400
Xiaoshi.

00:26:59.759 --> 00:27:01.559
Fine, I can't be bothered talking to you.

00:27:03.000 --> 00:27:04.000
The client is waiting for you.

00:27:04.279 --> 00:27:04.839
Let's go.

00:27:08.160 --> 00:27:10.000
I didn't eat much of their duck.

00:27:10.599 --> 00:27:12.359
Those pancakes filled me up.

00:27:13.920 --> 00:27:15.480
Looking at it this way,

00:27:15.559 --> 00:27:17.160
getting to this level isn't that hard.

00:27:17.960 --> 00:27:20.680
Our Peng Le Xuan is a genuine century-old brand.

00:27:20.680 --> 00:27:21.799
If we pick the right model,

00:27:21.799 --> 00:27:23.319
we could achieve this within a year.

00:27:23.319 --> 00:27:24.200
No problem.

00:27:24.960 --> 00:27:25.799
Right, right.

00:27:25.799 --> 00:27:27.559
Their duck is actually pretty average.

00:27:29.160 --> 00:27:31.079
You guys only see that

00:27:31.079 --> 00:27:32.519
their duck isn't authentic.

00:27:32.559 --> 00:27:33.519
But you don't see

00:27:33.519 --> 00:27:35.319
their strategy of playing to their strengths?

00:27:35.440 --> 00:27:36.680
Those flaky pancakes

00:27:36.680 --> 00:27:39.279
are from a family-run workshop in Suzhou.

00:27:39.559 --> 00:27:41.160
They only source from that one shop nationwide.

00:27:41.400 --> 00:27:43.279
The rice wine is from Wuxi.

00:27:43.400 --> 00:27:45.680
I think their attention to detail is very thoughtful.

00:27:46.680 --> 00:27:48.440
We're just getting started.

00:27:49.000 --> 00:27:51.200
Weiguo has rich business experience.

00:27:51.319 --> 00:27:53.160
Listening to him is... not wrong.

00:27:57.519 --> 00:27:58.640
We continue tomorrow.

00:28:00.079 --> 00:28:00.680
Hold on.

00:28:00.680 --> 00:28:01.680
I have to continue too.

00:28:01.680 --> 00:28:02.640
You continue.

00:28:12.079 --> 00:28:13.440
Lao Tong, come here, come here.

00:28:14.000 --> 00:28:15.079
I need to talk to you.

00:28:16.880 --> 00:28:18.960
I see you running around outside every day.

00:28:18.960 --> 00:28:20.319
Must have talked to a lot of clients.

00:28:22.359 --> 00:28:23.880
Not bad, not bad.

00:28:23.880 --> 00:28:26.480
"Not bad" means a lot of deposits.

00:28:26.480 --> 00:28:27.720
When will they be secured?

00:28:28.279 --> 00:28:31.000
I haven't had any big clients recently.

